The paper discusses a compiler for quantum programming languages, which falls under the category of programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The focus of the paper is on noisy intermediate-scale quantum (NISQ) systems, which are a specific type of quantum computing hardware, making the paper relevant to the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and constraints, which are relevant to the categories of algorithms and complexity (cs.AR) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses a solver to optimize the compilation process, which is relevant to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
